===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*p(r/j)a||skin}} (STEDT). This form likely represents the root while {{och-l|皮}} is its derivative with a voicing prefix, most likely PST *''m-'', found in several OC words for body parts like {{och-l|鼻|nose|tr=*'''m-'''bi[t]-s}}, {{och-l|肚|belly|tr=*'''m-'''tˤaʔ}}, {{och-l|右|right-hand|tr=*[ɢ]ʷəʔ-s (~ *'''m-'''qʷəʔ)}} and {{och-l|頭|head|tr=*['''m-'''t]ˤo}} ({{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart, 2014}}).

